"Applications that rely on the camera will temporarily disable Gaze Detection when used.
Device performance, low light, and wearing glasses may reduce its effectiveness. You can stop Gaze Detection at any time."
Using Voice Access in noisy or public spaces can be challenging. When Gaze Detection is switched on, Voice Access will ignore commands unless it thinks you are looking at your device.
Gaze Detection does not store or record any images from your camera, and never sends them to Google. The gaze icon will show when your attention is being detected.
